37 2. A person commits the offense of nonconsensual dissemination of private sexual
38 images if he or she:
39 (1) Intentionally disseminates an image with the intent to harass, threaten, or coerce
40 another person:
41 (a) [Who is at least eighteen years of age;
42 (b)] Who is identifiable from the image itself or information displayed in connection
43 with the image; and
44 [(c)] (b) Who is engaged in a sexual act or whose intimate parts are exposed, in whole
45 or in part;
46 (2) Obtains the image under circumstances in which a reasonable person would know
47 or understand that the image was to remain private; and
48 (3) Knows or should have known that the person in the image did not consent to the
49 dissemination.
50 3. The following activities are exempt from the provisions of this section:
51 (1) The intentional dissemination of an image of another identifiable person who is
52 engaged in a sexual act or whose intimate parts are exposed if the dissemination is made for
53 the purpose of a criminal investigation that is otherwise lawful;
54 (2) The intentional dissemination of an image of another identifiable person who is
55 engaged in a sexual act or whose intimate parts are exposed if the dissemination is for the
56 purpose of, or in connection with, the reporting of unlawful conduct;
57 (3) The intentional dissemination of an image of another identifiable person who is
58 engaged in a sexual act or whose intimate parts are exposed if the image involves voluntary
59 exposure in a public or commercial setting; or
60 (4) The intentional dissemination of an image of another identifiable person who is
61 engaged in a sexual act or whose intimate parts are exposed if the dissemination serves a
62 lawful public purpose.
63 4. Nothing in this section shall be construed to impose liability upon the following
64 entities solely as a result of content or information provided by another person:
65 (1) An interactive computer service, as defined in 47 U.S.C. Section 230(f)(2);
66 (2) A provider of public mobile services or private mobile radio services; or
67 (3) A telecommunications network or broadband provider.
68 5. A person convicted under this section is subject to the forfeiture provisions under
69 sections 513.600 to 513.660.
70 6. The offense of nonconsensual dissemination of private sexual images is a class D
71 felony, unless the image was of a minor or of a vulnerable person, in which case it is a
72 class C felony.

HB 2551 10
73 7. In addition to the criminal penalties listed in subsection 6 of this section, the person
74 in violation of the provisions of this section shall also be subject to a private cause of action
75 from the depicted person. Any successful private cause of action brought under this
76 subsection shall result in an award equal to ten thousand dollars or actual damages, whichever
77 is greater, and in addition shall include attorney's fees. Humiliation or embarrassment shall
78 be an adequate showing that the plaintiff has incurred damages; however, no physical
79 manifestation of either humiliation or embarrassment is necessary for damages to be shown.
573.112. 1. A person commits the offense of threatening the nonconsensual
